<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3242</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d527fn1">Sent via the Legation in China.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Omsk</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-18"><hi rend="italic">November 18,
                                        1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November
                                        19, 2.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>193. Early this morning three Social Revolutionary members of the
                                all-Russian Directory were arrested by Cossacks supposedly of
                                monarchical tendencies. No bloodshed. Omsk quiet to-day. Siberian
                                soldiers are going front in large numbers.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_HEL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>